  "prompt": "What are some tips on making it through the job interview process at Owens-Illinois?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for interviewing at Owens-Illinois:\n\n1. Research the company\n- Learn about their glass manufacturing operations\n- Understand their core business and recent company developments\n- Review their mission and values\n\n2. Prepare for common interview questions\n- Practice discussing your relevant experience\n- Be ready to explain your technical skills\n- Highlight your teamwork and problem-solving abilities\n\n3. Technical knowledge\n- If applying for a manufacturing or engineering role, be prepared to discuss technical skills\n- Show familiarity with manufacturing processes and safety standards\n\n4. Demonstrate relevant skills\n- Emphasize experience in manufacturing, quality control, or related fields\n- Show knowledge of manufacturing equipment and processes\n- Highlight safety consciousness\n\n5. Professional presentation\n- Dress professionally and appropriately\n- Bring extra copies of your resume\n- Show enthusiasm and positive attitude\n- Demonstrate good communication skills\n\n6. Ask informed questions\n- Inquire about specific roles and responsibilities\n- Ask about company culture and growth opportunities\n- Show genuine interest in the position\n\n7. Follow up\n- Send a thank-you email after the interview\n- Reiterate your interest in the position\n\nRemember that specific advice can vary depending on the specific role and department you're interviewing for.",
